Test Case 

example0.png

----------------------------------------------------------------
Input all candidate words (separated by <space> or ,): 
buys,book,year,lane,hold,search,ginger,syntax,symbol,car,ant,has,big,bus,beast
----------------------------------------------------------------
Index each slot with a number (starting form 1)
and input index with their length in pair (with 0 0 to stop).
e.g. 1 4 (Enter) -> word 1 requires 4 letters
1 4     
2 6
3 4
4 3
5 3
0 0
----------------------------------------------------------------
Input each cross in the form i, j, k, m, which means
for example, if slot 1 (across) and slot 3 (down) has its 4th letter
across 3-down's 2nd letter, then input 1 3 4 2 (Enter). (Use 0 0 0 0 to finish).
1 3 3 1
2 3 3 3
2 4 5 1
2 5 1 3
1 5 1 1
0 0 0 0

